[I] A libc for WebAssembly programs built on top of WASI system calls

[T] WASI Libc is a libc for WebAssembly programs built on top of WASI system
[T] calls. It provides a wide array of POSIX-compatible C APIs, including
[T] support for standard I/O, file I/O, filesystem manipulation, memory
[T] management, time, string, environment variables, program startup, and
[T] many other APIs.

[U] https://wasi.dev/

[A] WebAssembly CG
[M] Rene Rebe <rene@t2-project.org>

[C] base/development
[F] CROSS NO-SSP NO-LTO NO-PIE OBJDIR
[R] - alpha hppa hppa64 ia64

[L] APL MIT
[V] 31
[P] X -----5---9 152.500

[D] e3b6a9f66cdded87d79623e0f16ec04a93025797c71bc2c7a9b20eb8 wasi-sdk-31.tar.gz https://github.com/WebAssembly/wasi-libc/archive/refs/tags/

[ $prefix_auto = 1 ] && prefix=opt/wasi && set_confopt
. $base/package/*/*/wasi.in

CC=${archprefix}clang AR=llvm-ar NM=llvm-nm

var_append cmakeopt ' ' -DCMAKE_C_COMPILER=$CC
var_append cmakeopt ' ' -DCHECK_SYMBOLS=OFF
var_append cmakeopt ' ' -DCMAKE_C_LINKER_DEPFILE_SUPPORTED=OFF
var_append cmakeopt ' ' -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=$root/$prefix

hook_add inmake 5 "mkdir -p sysroot/share"
